            <title>[JCR-3248] TimeoutHandler visitor should be extracted into a dedicated class</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-3248</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>This is a minor problem that I&amp;#39;ve stumbled upon when looking at a memory leak.&lt;br/&gt;
It seems that the TimeoutHandler thread runs each second and it uses a custom ElementVisitor to do its business. By creating a new instance of ElementVisitor each second this creates some garbage that could be avoided by using a predefined class.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Short story: during a unit test it creates 3x instances each second that have 16 bytes each. Having a dedicated visitor class creates just 3 instances for the lifespan of the repository.</description>
